4 SYNOPSIS:
5 This bill would establish an investment program
6 to provide financial support for trade programs in the
7 State of Alabama.
8 This bill would incentivize donations to local
9 foundations that support the development of career
10 technical education by creating a tax credit for
11 individuals and entities to offset their state income,
12 excise, premium, and utility tax liability. Qualifying
13 entities would use these donations to pay for the
14 construction and development of trade programs for
15 local industry. These funds may be used for
16 construction of facilities, including expenditures to
17 maintain or upgrade facilities.
18 This bill would also establish a board within
19 the Alabama Department of Workforce to determine the
20 eligibility of qualifying entities to receive donations
21 that qualify for the tax credit and to operate the
22 program with the support of the Department of Revenue.
23
