57 Alabama 1975.
58 (7) INCOME TAX. The taxes levied and collected pursuant
59 to Chapter 18 of Title 40, Code of Alabama 1975.
60 (8) INSURANCE PREMIUM TAX. The taxes levied and
61 collected pursuant to Chapter 4A of Title 27, Code of Alabama
62 1975.
63 (9) PROGRAM. The Prepare Alabama Investment Program.
64 (10) QUALIFIED DONATION. An unrestricted transfer of
65 funds from a qualified donor to an eligible entity.
66 (11) QUALIFIED DONOR. Any person who makes a qualified
67 donation to an eligible entity.
68 (12) TRADE SCHOOL. A public or private educational
69 institution or entity that is approved by a state agency or
70 subdivision of the state or accredited by a state-recognized
71 or nationally recognized accrediting body to provide
72 technical, trade, or vocational training.
73 (13) TAX YEAR. The calendar year for which annual
74 income is reported to the State of Alabama by a person that
75 makes a qualified donation.
76 (14) UTILITY TAX. The taxes levied and collected
77 pursuant to Sections 40-21-82 through 40-21-107, Code of
78 Alabama 1975.
79 Section 3. (a) The Prepare Alabama Investment Program
80 Board is established within the department to oversee the
81 development and operation of the Prepare Alabama Investment
82 Program. The board shall consist of the following members:
83 (1) The Governor, or his or her designee.
84 (2) The Secretary of the Alabama Department of
