92 (6) Two representatives of the Economic Development
93 Partnership of Alabama (EDPA), appointed by the organization.
94 (b) Members shall be appointed within 30 days of the
95 effective date of this act.
96 (c)(1) The EDPA shall appoint one initial member to the
97 board for a term of two years and one initial member to the
98 board for a term of four years.
99 (2) A member subsequently appointed to the board by the
100 EDPA shall serve for a term of four years.
101 (3) A vacancy on the board of a representative of the
102 EDPA shall be filled by the EDPA before the next scheduled
103 meeting of the board, and the appointee shall serve for the
104 remainder of the unexpired term.
105 (d) Designees or appointees to the board shall be
106 inclusive and reflect the racial, gender, geographic, urban,
107 rural, and economic diversity of the state.
108 (e)(1) No later than three months after the effective
109 date of this act, the Governor, or his or her designee, shall
110 call the first meeting of the board, at which the members
111 shall elect a chair.
112 (2) The board shall meet at least once a year in
