128 Section 4. To receive qualified donations as an
129 eligible entity under the program, the entity shall meet all
130 of the following requirements:
131 (1) Be a public or private trade school or trade
132 program recognized and approved by the department, or be a
133 community development foundation.
134 (2) Provide instructional services in trades designated
135 by the department without discrimination.
136 (3) Be in compliance with all reports and audits
137 required by law.
138 (4) Submit to the board a written five-year plan that
139 describes the financial viability and stability of the entity,
140 with a plan detailing how it would use qualified donations
Page 5

with a plan detailing how it would use qualified donations
SB111 INTRODUCED
141 under the program and update the written plan five years after
142 the initial plan is submitted and every five years thereafter.
143 Section 5. The board shall do all of the following:
144 (1) By November 1 of each year, determine if an
145 organization, school, or foundation is an eligible entity
146 pursuant to Section 4.
147 (2) By December 1 of each year, submit the list of
148 eligible entities to the Department of Revenue.
149 (3) By December 31 of each year, publish a list of
150 entities eligible to receive qualified donations during the
151 next tax year on its website or on the department's website.
152 Section 6. (a) An eligible entity shall only use
153 qualified donations for the purpose of providing workforce
154 focused instruction to the residents of the area that it
155 serves, which may include operational expenditures and
156 expenditures for maintenance, capital upgrades, and
157 improvements.
158 (b) An eligible entity may retain a person to solicit
159 or manage the qualified donations it receives for a percentage
160 fee of the qualified donations solicited or managed, but total
161 fees may not exceed three percent of the total amount of
162 qualified donations received during a calendar year.
163 (c) By March 1 of each year, an eligible entity shall
164 file a report with the board, on a form to be developed by the
165 board that shall include all of the following information:
166 (1) A schedule of each qualifying donation received
167 during the preceding tax year, which includes the amount,
168 identifies the qualified donor, and describes how the
Page 6

identifies the qualified donor, and describes how the
